ated Party Transactions", "bbox": [84.4, 860.7, 421.1, 883.7]}, {"text": "On December 31, 2018, the Company completed the sale of its pressure pumping assets to ProPetro in exchange for 16.6", "bbox": [140.7, 904.4, 1159.2, 927.5]}, {"text": "million shares of ProPetro common stock and $110 million of short-term receivables to be paid by ProPetro during the first quarter", "bbox": [84.4, 929.4, 1158.8, 952.5]}, {"text": "of 2019. The shares acquired in the acquisition represent approximately 16 percent of ProPetro's outstanding common stock,", "bbox": [84.4, 954.4, 1153.8, 977.5]}, {"text": "resulting in ProPetro being considered a related party as of December 31, 2018. In addition to the sale of equipment and related", "bbox": [84.4, 979.4, 1158.8, 1002.5]}, {"text": "facilities, the Company entered into a long-term agreement with ProPetro to provide pressure pumping and related services. See", "bbox": [84.4, 1004.5, 1154.0, 1027.5]}, {"text": "Note 2 and Note 3 for additional information.", "bbox": [84.4, 1029.5, 464.2, 1052.5]}, {"text": "In February 2019, the Company exercised its right to designate (i) a director to the board of directors of ProPetro, which", "bbox": [140.7, 1073.2, 1159.2, 1096.3]}, {"text": "right will exist for so long as the Company owns five percent or more of ProPetro’s outstanding common stock, and (ii) an", "bbox": [84.4, 1098.2, 1159.2, 1121.3]}, {"text": "independent director to the board of directors of ProPetro, which is a one time right. Mark S. Berg, the Company’s Executive Vice", "bbox": [84.4, 1123.2, 1153.6, 1146.3]}, {"text": "President Corporate/Vertically Integrated Operations, was the Company’s designee in the first category, and Royce W. Mitchell,", "bbox": [84.4, 1148.3, 1159.3, 1171.3]}, {"text": "an independent member of the Company’s board of directors, was the Company’s designee in the second category.", "bbox": [84.4, 1173.3, 1039.2, 1196.3]}, {"text": "Balances with the Company's affiliate are as follows:", "bbox": 